<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>It doesn't take much for her to turn heads.</p>

<p>And Irina Shayk was at it again on Wednesday as she made her way through New York City.</p>

<p>The catwalk queen, 34, flashed her runway legs in a tiny pair of shorts and knee-high snake print boots.</p>

<p>Model behavior! Irina Shayk was at it again on Wednesday as she took the streets of New York City by storm</p>

<p>Irina oozed confidence as she strutted through the Big Apple in her revealing yet trendy outfit.</p>

<p>While flashing her legs with a tiny pair of shorts, she covered up the remained of her body with an over-sized 032c sweatshirt.</p>

<p>The model tucked a slim pair of shades into her neckline while carrying a majority of her belongings inside her leather purse, which hung off her shoulder.</p>

<p>Irina did not wear a face mask, but she did have one on her.</p>

<p>Selfie game strong: Holding the phone at arms-length, Irina served a model-esque expression towards the camera </p>

<p>Walk this way: Shayk turned heads as she strutted through the Big Apple </p>

<p>The model's stunning complexion was put on full display as she slicked her brunette tresses back into a neat little bun, while accessorizing with gold hoop earrings.</p>

<p>At one point, Irina appeared to stop for a selfie.   </p>

<p>Holding the phone at arms-length, Irina served a model-esque expression towards the camera.</p>

<p>Legs for days: Shayk worked a stylish pair of snake print boots </p>

<p>Irina did not appear to be joined by her three-year-old daughter Lea, whom she shares with her ex-boyfriend Bradley Cooper.</p>

<p>The couple split after four years together last year, and have been co-parenting Lea together ever since.</p>

<p>Bradley recently revealed he had been teaching their daughter how to swim in his bathtub while caring for his mother Gloria Campano at home.</p>

<p>'I'm with my daughter and my mother and my two dogs, and we have not left the house,' he said in a discussion with Interview Magazine. 'My mother is going to be 80, and she has a colostomy bag, so I can't let anybody in the house. And I can't leave the house, because if she gets it, it's over.'</p>

<p>'We live in a little townhouse, thankfully there's a backyard. I'm running a one-man preschool. We get up, we do swim class in the bathtub.'</p>

